Tasks:

Install latest CentOS 7 distribution on hypervisor of your choosing.
Configure user "Name_Surname" during installation (substitute Name and Surname with your credentials).
Configure network during installation.
Configure custom sizes for "/home", "/opt", "/var" directories during installation.
Self-review:

You are able to login into VM using user "Name_Surname".
You are able to access internet from your VM.
Command "df -h" in terminal reflects the sizes you set for "/home", "/opt", "/var" directories.
Helpful materials:

https://docs.centos.org/en-US/centos/install-guide/Simple_Installation/
